org.hfoss.posit.util
Class DataPoint

java.lang.Object
  org.hfoss.posit.util.DataPoint

public class DataPoint
extends java.lang.Object

DataPoint is supposed to be a generic term for representing data items in posit for maps. Since a variety of data items/types are dealt with in the form of records or different occurrences of records (often referred to as "sightings"), it is necessary to have a data structure to represent them automatically in the required map and to loosely couple them together.

Author:
Prasanna Gautam
